Return value of send is not checked on owner2.send(sum2) and owner.send(balance)

External calls to the token contract via low-level call() and to owner/owner2 via send() are not handled properly. If c.call for transferFrom fails, tokens_buy returns false without reverting (users lose ETH and no tokens are sent). The owner2.send and owner.send calls can also fail silently and lock ether in the contract, preventing withdrawals.

Low-level call to external token contract using .call without proper handling of failure or revert. The fallback does not revert on call failure, causing users to lose ETH while tokens are not transferred.
